      "side": 1,
      "message": "This path cannot overwrite a declined request: when oldReq exists the function returns unconditionally, declined or not (the line right below this comment). A declined entry is also protected in addConversationRequest(): when an entry already exists, an incoming non-declined request hits `if (!req.declined) return false;` and is ignored — only decline markers coming from device sync may update the entry. This patch did not change either guard: a tombstoned conversation now passes the initial isAcceptedConversation() check, but a previously declined request still blocks both the onConversationRequest path (unconditional return) and the onTrustRequest path (addConversationRequest returns false). A replayed or stale invite therefore cannot undo a local decline. The suggested diff would actually relax the current behavior by letting newer requests bypass a decline, which is the opposite of the stated concern.",
